content.text:
I'm showing you three screenshots from our RDR2 companion app:

1. Home page (first image) - this is our main landing page and establishes the overall UI style
2. Weapons section landing page (second image) - links to different weapon tools
3. Horses section landing page (third image) - links to different horse tools

For the section landing pages (weapons and horses), I want to:
- Make everything fit above the fold (no scrolling needed)
- Improve the layout to be more visually appealing
- Keep consistent with the home page's western/RDR2 aesthetic

Please give me specific, actionable recommendations for improving the weapons and horses landing pages. Consider layout, spacing, card sizes, and visual hierarchy.
